        <p> <strong> Congratulations on taking the next step to welcoming a new companion into your home! </strong> </p>
        <p>
            While cats are generally more independent than some other pets, they still require proper care and attention, and it's important
            to research and understand their needs fully before bringing one home. A well-balanced diet, stimluating environment, regular vet
            checks &amp; vaccinations, and bonding &amp; training sessions are all things to consider when thinking about the maintenance and wellbeing
            of any animal, including cats. If you're considering blending cat ownership into your lifestyle, or if you've recently adopted and
            feel lost, here's a small compilation of public resources and some of our shelter's tips to caring for a cat to help you decide!
        </p>
